24/07/2006
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- A senior Bulgarian delegation that includes Defence Minister Vesselin Bliznakov and Bulgarian Army chief General Zlatan Stoykov arrived for a one-day visit to Bosnia and Herzegovina on Monday (24 July).
Their schedule included a stop at the Sarajevo base of Butmir, where 130 Bulgarian troops are serving in the EU mission Althea in BiH, and meetings with high-ranking EUFOR officers.
In other news, Bliznakov announced on Sunday that Bulgaria will participate in a collective deal with other six NATO members states for the purchase of two strategic transportation C-17 aircraft.
He said the project can be realised as part of a wider NATO programme for strategic transportation.
(Darik, Bulgarian Government website, Monitor - 24/07/06;
bTV - 23/07/06)
